The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 India to host

New Delhi: After a gap of 25 years, India will host the mens hockey World Cup in 2010, the year when the Commonwealth Games will also be held in the country. 

Although India had already been sounded as a possible venue for the event, the games world governing body has now officially communicated to the Indian Hockey Federation. The Dhyanchand National Stadium would be the venue of the tournament to be held in February 2010. 

 (PTI) 




